ABOUT
-----

The UC Berkeley Schedule Enhancer (UCBSE) is a User Script for 
Greasemonkey which improves the layout making it easier to read and 
search for classes.


INSTALLING
----------

(1.) The first thing you need is the Firefox web browser which can be 
	 downloaded at http://www.firefox.com/. If you don't like Firefox,
	 see the section on Support for Other Browsers.
(2.) After you have installed Firefox, the next thing you need is the 
	 Greasemonkey plugin which can be downloaded at http://www.greasespot.net/. 
(3.) After you have installed Greasemonkey, you need to install the 
	 User Script. To install it, go to 
	 http://userscripts.org/scripts/show/105611 and click "Install". 

Now you can start using UCBSE!


SUPPORT FOR OTHER BROWSERS
--------------------------

There are Gresemonkey equivalents for other browsers. You can read more
about it here: 

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greasemonkey#Equivalents_for_other_browsers



REPORTING BUGS
--------------

If something looks funny or information is missing, please report it
so we can fix the bug as soon as possible! 

The best way to report bugs is to (1.) tell us the exact phrases you
entered into the search boxes, (2.) tell us the Course Control 
Number to give us a location of where the script went wrong, or (3.) 
send us a screenshot.

Please report all bugs here: http://userscripts.org/scripts/issues/105611


CONTRIBUTING
------------

If you would like to contribute and help improve the UCBSE, feel free
to make changes by making a fork of the repository on github and sending 
me a pull request.

How can you help?
	- Optimize the regular expressions.
	- Reduce interaction with the DOM.
	- Fix bugs!
	- Improve UI.


GITHUB
------

The repository is located at: 
	https://github.com/athk/UCBSE
